He is the lily of the valley. He is the fairest of ten thousand.

00:28:25.040 --> 00:28:46.273
And as I saw the waterfalls falling off the cliffs and the mountains and the snow caps because it looked like it was turning into spring, the Lord said, 'I want you to pay attention to these flowers for it is symbolic of something.'He said, 'Look into it.'So I've had so many people try to help.

00:28:46.274 --> 00:28:58.968
What does the daffodil represent? This is a representation of spring coming. The Holy Ghost is telling me a great harvest is coming.

00:28:58.969 --> 00:29:10.943
As I saw the people marching through the valley, joining up with Jesus in a single file line, following our friend, following our king, our maker, as he was going through the valley.

00:29:10.944 --> 00:29:22.773
As I watched him, he went all through Europe to each place. Then he went through the Middle East, down through Africa, through South America, and through America.

00:29:22.774 --> 00:29:30.039
He went around and was knocking on every one of our hearts: 'Will you let me in?

00:29:30.040 --> 00:29:38.158
Will you accept me as Lord and Savior?'But he was a gentleman about it. He waited a little bit.

00:29:38.159 --> 00:29:44.959
He looked around to see if the person would answer the door, but he didn't force his way in.

00:29:44.960 --> 00:29:48.459
He didn't knock the door down and say, 'You're getting saved, buddy.

00:29:48.460 --> 00:29:53.559
Get out here. Come on. We're going.'He waited patiently to see if they would answer.

00:29:53.560 --> 00:30:03.079
But as he waited, he sat there with expectation on his face. 'Will you just let me in?

00:30:03.080 --> 00:30:11.119
I want to be your savior. I want you to follow me. Come follow me.'I figured this is how he did it with the disciples.

00:30:11.120 --> 00:30:23.523
'Come follow me. I'll make you a fisher of men. Come follow me, Matthew.'And as he would go through the towns and the places, the disciples followed him.

00:30:23.524 --> 00:30:28.270
